                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350921-1957-offence-1 t18350921-name-259"></join>Charles Knapp</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-260" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-260" type="surname" value="KNAPP"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-260" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES KNAPP</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a general salesman, and live in St. James's-street, Marylebone. On the 24th of August, the prisoner came to my shop and paid me some money—she returned in an hour and a half. and bought a flat-iron for sixpence—I missed a wine-glass from my counter and saw it in her basket, which she had in her hand—I then found it two shirts—I asked what reason she had to take them—she said if I would let her go, she would pay me for them—I gave her in charge—they have my mark on them—she was searched at the station-house, and two silk handkerchiefs were found in her pocket—they are mine, and are worth fifteen shillings all together.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Used she to deal at your shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, for a considerable time, and paid for the articles by instalments—I have heard her husband is in distress—she bore a respectable cha<lb></lb>racter—she has four children.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-261" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-261" type="surname" value="LONERGRAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-261" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LONERGRAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 49.) I was called to Mr. Knapp's shop, and found the prisoner there—I found two silk handkerchiefs on her and thirteen duplicates—she said if Mr. Knapp would forgive her, she would pay for the property.</p>
